Task Management Module Update Feature Description

Feature Description: A new unified "Task Management" module has been added, supporting batch task assignment, modification of task deadlines, and other operations for multiple files. All workflows for every file under a project can be displayed on a unified panel, without the need to click on document details to switch between workflows.

【Task Management】List Description:
After uploading files, clicking "Assign Task" will redirect the page to the 【Task Management】list. When there are a large number of files in a project, initializing the 【Task Management】list may take some time.

View all workflows for project files: By default, when entering the 【Task Management】list, all files and tasks under the first workflow of the project are retrieved. Using the "Workflow" dropdown above the list, you can select specific workflows such as "Translation" or "Proofreading" to view details. Selecting "All" allows you to view all workflows for all files.

View task status: Upon first entering the 【Task Management】list, all task statuses are "Unassigned." Once a task is assigned, its status changes to "Incomplete" (indicated by a "small clock" icon).

When there are many tasks under a project, you can quickly locate "Unassigned," "Assigned," or "Incomplete" tasks using the "Task Status" filter:

Quickly locate specific tasks based on target language and other filter criteria: In multilingual projects, when there are numerous files and many tasks across different workflows in the task list, you can use the "Filter" function to quickly pinpoint tasks with a specific target language or file name:

【Task Management】Operation Instructions:
Split File: On this 【Task Management】page, document splitting based on workflow is still supported. Click the "Split" button and choose the number of parts to split into from the popup window:

Since entering the 【Task Management】page will automatically create "initial tasks" for each file based on the project workflow by default, the following popup will appear when splitting tasks. You can ignore it and click "Confirm" in the popup.

Once the file is split, the split tasks will be displayed in the task management list. The project lead can then further assign the tasks covering specific segment ranges to team members.

Merge File: Split tasks can be re-merged. Consecutively split tasks under the same file and same workflow can be merged. If the split tasks have already been assigned to relevant members, the assignment will be canceled upon merging.

Assign Task: In the task list, click the "Assign" button under the "Name" field to assign the current task to a team member.

In the new task assignment popup, you can also see the member's current workload within the selected time period.
Furthermore, the new 【Task Management】list supports batch assignment, i.e., bulk assigning tasks within the same workflow to the same member. For example, if you currently need one translator to handle two tasks in the "Translation" workflow, you can select the tasks and click the "Assign" button above the list:

The effect after batch assignment is shown in the image:

After assigning a task to a member, if you need to change the translator, you can click the "small pencil" icon next to the member's name and re-designate the member responsible for that translation task in the "Assign Task" popup.

Preview Task: In the 【Task Management】list, users can also preview the segment content of the current task. Click the "Preview" button next to the workflow name to view the specific segment content of that task in the file within a popup.